## Quick Start

1. Clone or download this repository and open the folder in VS Code:

   - In VS Code press Ctrl+K then O (Ctrl+K, O) and select the project folder.

2. Obtain a WAQI API token:

   - Get your token at: https://aqicn.org/data-platform/token/
   - Read API usage details at: https://aqicn.org/api/

3. Insert your token:

   - Open script.js and replace the value of the API_KEY constant with your token:
     const API_KEY = "YOUR_TOKEN_HERE";
   - Do not commit your token to a public repository. Use environment variables or secrets for production.

4. Install the Live Server extension (if not already installed):

   - In VS Code, open Extensions, search for "Live Server" by Ritwick Dey and install it.
   - Or visit: https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ritwickdey.LiveServer

5. Run the app:
   - Right-click index.html in VS Code and choose "Open with Live Server".
   - Or use Live Server's "Go Live" button in the status bar.

## File Structure

- index.html — root HTML file for the single page app
- index.css — styling (dark theme, variables for easy customization)
- script.js — fetches data from WAQI and updates the UI

## Theme & Styling Notes

- Dark base: charcoal (#222428 / #2b2f31)
- Accent: #ff4500
- Primary text: near-white for contrast
- Subtle gray scales for secondary text
- CSS variables are used in index.css so you can change the palette easily:
  --bg, --card-bg, --accent, --text, --muted, etc.

## WAQI API Quick Reference

- Feed by city:
  GET https://api.waqi.info/feed/{city}/?token={token}
  Example: https://api.waqi.info/feed/delhi/?token=YOUR_TOKEN
- Responses include fields like aqi, idx, dominentpol, time, iaqi.{pm25,o3,...}

Important: WAQI API policies

- Respect usage limits and attribution requirements. See the WAQI API docs: https://aqicn.org/api/
- Attribution: Follow WAQI's attribution requirements if you publish the data publicly.

## Security & Privacy

- Do not commit your API token to a public repo.
- For sharing the project publicly, remove the token from script.js and instruct users to supply their own token.
- Consider using a server-side proxy or environment variables to keep tokens secret.

## Customization & Tips

- Change the accent color by editing --accent in index.css.
- Add more metrics (PM2.5 history, pollutant breakdown) by querying the API response's iaqi object.
- Add geolocation support: use navigator.geolocation to obtain coordinates and call the WAQI feed by geo: https://api.waqi.info/feed/geo:{lat};{lon}/?token={token}

## Troubleshooting

- If you see CORS or 403 errors: ensure your token is valid and you are using the correct endpoint.
- If Live Server doesn't open: check the extension is enabled and reload VS Code.
- If the API returns an error object, script.js shows a notification in the UI. Check console logs for more details.

